heading: addition UID
xpath: (//tei:additions/tei:p/(node())[1]|//tei:additions/tei:note/(node())[1]|//tei:additions[not(tei:p or tei:note)]/(node())[1]|//tei:additions/(text()[../tei:p or ../tei:note][not(normalize-space(.)="")])[1])/concat(ancestor::tei:TEI/tei:teiHeader/tei:fileDesc/tei:publicationStmt/tei:idno[@type="msID"], "_addition_", count(preceding::tei:p[ancestor::tei:additions]|preceding::tei:note[ancestor::tei:additions]|preceding::tei:additions[not(tei:p or tei:note)]|preceding::tei:additions[tei:p or tei:note][text()]) + 1)
comment: A unique identifier for the addition, generated by concatenating the identifier given to the manuscript with which the addition is associated with a count of how many addition elements precede the current element in the entry file.

heading: file URL
comment: A unique identifier for the catalogue file, given in the xml:id attribute to the TEI root element.

heading: collection
comment: The collection in which the manuscript is recorded, given in an idno element within the publicationStmt element which has @type "collection" and is not an alternative identifier (and therefore has no @subtype with "alt").

heading: ms ID
comment: The identifier given to the manuscript, given in an idno element within the publicationStmt element which has @type "msID" and is not an alternative identifier (and therefore has no @subtype with "alt").

heading: shelfmark
comment: The shelfmark given to the manuscript, given in an idno element within the publicationStmt element which has @type "shelfmark" and is not an alternative identifier (and therefore has no @subtype with "alt").

heading: ms type
comment: Whether the current row concerns a fragment ('fragment'), a manuscript part ('part'), an entire manuscript ('manuscript'), a manuscript containing parts ('manuscript-composite') or a manuscript containing fragments ('manuscript-with-fragment').

heading: part name
comment: The identifier given to the manuscript or manuscript part in an idno element which has @type "part" and is not an alternative identifier (and therefore has no @subtype with "alt").

heading: partID
comment: The identifier given to the manuscript or manuscript part in an xml:id attribute. If the current row is not for a fragment or a manuscript part, this column will be the same as the metadata: ID column.

heading: additions
comment: An overview of the current addition, as encoded within the additions element.

heading: locus
comment: Details of any locus information for this feature encoded within a locus element. When multiple loci are given, they are separated using a semi-colon.

heading: from
comment: The folio, page, or membrane reference at which this feature begins, as encoded within the @from attribute to a locus element. Where multiple loci are given, they are separated by a space.

heading: to
comment: The folio, page, or membrane reference at which this feature ends, as encoded within the @to attribute to a locus element. Where multiple loci are given, they are separated by a space.

heading: author name(s)
comment: Details of any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as an author through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: author ID(s)
comment: The identifier(s), corresponding to those found in the authority file, given for any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as an author through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: scribe name(s)
comment: Details of any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as a scribe through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: scribe ID(s)
comment: The identifier(s), corresponding to those found in the authority file, given for any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as a scribe through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: signer name(s)
comment: Details of any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as a signer through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: signer ID(s)
comment: The identifier(s), corresponding to those found in the authority file, given for any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as a signer through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: former owner name(s)
comment: Details of any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as a former owner through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: former owner ID(s)
comment: The identifier(s), corresponding to those found in the authority file, given for any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element and identified as a former owner through an appropriate @role attribute.

heading: other person name(s)
comment: Details of any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element who is not assigned a role through a @role attribute.

heading: other person ID(s)
comment: The identifier(s), corresponding to those found in the authority file, given for any person(s) named within the additions information within a persName element who is not assigned a role through a @role attribute.

heading: bibl(s)
comment: All bibliographic references associated with this feature, as encoded within bibl elements.

heading: title(s)
comment: All titles of works associated with this feature, as encoded within title elements.

heading: ref(s)
comment: All references associated with this feature, as encoded within ref elements.

heading: ref URI(s)
comment: URIs for all references associated with this feature, as encoded within @target attributes to ref elements.
